          "author_association": "OWNER",
          "body": "Filed from the pd-book-tools deep code/security review.\n\n    Report: `pd-book-tools/docs/research/2026-05-22-deep-code-security-review.md`\n    Finding: #14\n\n    ## Summary\n\n    Each illustration region independently chooses a caption, so nearby regions can reuse the same caption words.\n\n    ## Impact\n\n    Downstream text/layout output can duplicate captions.\n\n    ## Evidence\n\n    - `pd_book_tools/ocr/layout_aware_reorg.py:840`\n- `pd_book_tools/ocr/layout_aware_reorg.py:846`\n- `pd_book_tools/ocr/layout_aware_reorg.py:879`\n\n    ## Acceptance\n\n    - [ ] Track consumed caption regions or word IDs.\n- [ ] Assign each caption to one nearest or most-overlapping illustration.\n- [ ] Add a two-figure one-caption regression test.\n\n    ## Notes\n\n    This issue was filed from a read-only review. Confirm behavior with a focused failing test before implementation where practical.",
          "closed_at": "2026-05-22T16:04:07Z",
